angular
ng g component NAME (from components folder) //creates new component

heroku stuff
https://vast-brook-94853.herokuapp.com/ | https://git.heroku.com/vast-brook-94853.git

app deployed on heroku
database hosted on mLab


HEROKU COMMANDS
git status					//see changed files
git add .					//stage files
git commit -m "comments"	//commit files
git push heroku master		//push files
heroku open 				//open app url
heroku local				//open app locally
heroku ps					//view dyno hours
heroku ps:scale web=0		//kill dyno
heroku ps:scale web=1		//restart dyno
heroku logs --tail			//view logs



MAKING CHANGES
mongod (bin)
mongo (root)
nodemon (root)
ng serve(angular-src)
ng build (after changes)
push it to heroku 